{{distinguish|text='''North Korea Review''', previously published by [[The Jamestown Foundation]]}} {{more citations needed|date=November 2016}} {{Infobox journal | title = North Korean Review | cover = North Korean Review.jpg | image_size = 175px | editor = Yongho Kim | discipline = [[North Korean studies]] | abbreviation = North Korean Rev. | publisher = The [[Institute for North Korean Studies]] and [[McFarland & Company|McFarland]] | country = United States | frequency = Biannual | history = 2005–present | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.northkoreanreview.net | link1 = | link1-name = | JSTOR = | OCLC = 55895634 | CODEN = | LCCN = | ISSN = 1551-2789 | eISSN = 1941-2886 }}'''''North Korean Review''''' is a biannual [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by the [[Institute for North Korean Studies]] (INKS), at the [[University of Detroit Mercy]] in the United States. The journal was established in 2005 by INKS and [[McFarland & Company]].<ref name=journals>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mcfarlandbooks.com/customers/journals/ |title=Journals |work=McFarlandBooks.com |publisher=[[McFarland & Company]] |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20150420040701/http://www.mcfarlandbooks.com/customers/journals/ |archivedate=20 April 2015 |deadurl=yes |df=dmy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=North Korean Review|url=https://www.northkoreanreview.net/about-us|website=NorthKoreanReview|accessdate=January 26, 2018|publisher=[[McFarland & Company]]}}</ref> It publishes policy-oriented articles, short papers, commentaries, and case studies on all aspects of [[North Korea]], including culture, history, economics, business, religion, politics, and international relations.
The editor of the journal is Yongho Kim, and the managing editor is Lonnie Edge.
The stated purpose of the journal is to provide an improved understanding of the complexity of North Korea. In March 2006, the ''[[Library Journal]]'' said that it is "the first journal of its kind" and that it "belongs in most university libraries".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.libraryjournal.com/article/CA6310129.html |title=Magazines |publisher=Libraryjournal.com |date= |accessdate=2012-01-04}}</ref>
