{{Infobox journal | title = Sign Systems Studies | cover = Sss33.1.jpg | image_size = 200px | formernames = Trudy po Znakovym Sistemam | editor = Kalevi Kull, Ene-Reet Soovik, Timo Maran, Silvi Salupere, Mihhail Lotman, Peeter Torop, Remo Gramigna | discipline = [[Semiotics]] | language = English, Russian, Estonian | abbreviation = | publisher = [[University of Tartu Press]] | country = Estonia | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1964–present | website = http://www.ut.ee/SOSE/sss/index.htm | link3 = http://www.sss.ut.ee/index.php/sss | link3-name = Open access (starting 2012) | link2 = http://www.pdcnet.org/signsystems/toc | link2-name = Online access | OCLC = 41123942 | JSTOR = | LCCN = sn99034172 | CODEN = | ISSN = 1406-4243 | eISSN = }} '''''Sign Systems Studies''''' is a [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] on [[semiotics]] edited at the Department of Semiotics of the [[University of Tartu]] and published by the [[University of Tartu Press]]. It is the oldest periodical in the field.<ref>''Semiotica'' 158(1/4): 25 (2006).</ref> It was initially published in [[Russian language|Russian]] and since 1998 in English with Russian and Estonian language abstracts. The journal was established by [[Juri Lotman]] as ''Trudy po Znakovym Sistemam'' in 1964. Since 1998 it has been edited by [[Kalevi Kull]], [[Mihhail Lotman]], and [[Peeter Torop]]. The journal is available online from the [[Philosophy Documentation Center]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pdcnet.org/signsystems/toc |title=Sign Systems Studies online|accessdate=18 August 2012}}</ref> indexed by [[Web of Science|WoS]] and [[Scopus]], and starting 2012 also on an [[open access]] platform.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sss.ut.ee/index.php/sss |title=Sign Systems Studies|accessdate=18 September 2014}}</ref>
